<p>I've come across a bug in our application where the following XHTML code doesn't work as I'd expect it!</p>  <pre><code>&lt;h:selectManyCheckbox value="#{nuv.rollen}" id="rollen" layout="pageDirection"&gt;     &lt;f:selectItems var="r" value="#{nuv.findRollen()}" itemLabel="#{r.label}" itemDisabled="#{nuv.isDisabledRolle(r)}" /&gt;     &lt;our:entityConverter /&gt;&lt;!-- translates our entities back and forth --&gt; &lt;/h:selectManyCheckbox&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The setter <code>nuv.setRollen(List)</code> is called with an empty list (at least if all items are disabled) although all disabled items are checked in the UI. The code assumes that all elements have been deselected. If the items are enabled everything works fine.</p>  <p>Is this behavior normal? I'm very confused about this.</p>